summary: Captain Marvel film headcanon. SPOILERS! So we’ve been told that the Supreme Intelligence (AI leader of Kree society) appears to...
body:
Captain Marvel film headcanon. SPOILERS!

So we’ve been told that the Supreme Intelligence (AI leader of Kree society) appears to each person as the individual they most respect. In the beginning of the film, Veers/Carol asks Yon-Rogg who the Supreme Intelligence appears to him as, teasing him that it’s Veers herself. Yon-Rogg doesn’t respond to her, since telling others such a thing is taboo. Wouldn’t it be funny if, when Yon-Rogg arrived back on Hala after being soundly beaten by Carol, who doesn’t feel the need to prove herself to him anymore, he went to report to the Supreme Intelligence about the debacle on C-53 and is surprised to see the person he admires the most has changed – now, the likeness of Carol Danvers has replaced them. Yon-Rogg, who has loyally been a dog of the Kree, lied for them, killed for them, realizes that the most powerful thing he’s ever witnessed isn’t the power Carol has – it’s her free will, her independence, her desire to right wrongs even if it means going against what she’s been taught.

Anyway, I think that would be cool.

summary: I mean I was just speaking on this on a post about Regina King, about how black women who play the best friend not-explicitly...
body:
I mean I was just speaking on this on a post about Regina King, about how black women who play the best friend not-explicitly canon-canon lover of the white female lead are so easily and quickly forgotten, no matter how present (more so the “token black best friend”. I do not personally believe Maria is a token character, yet, here we are).

Captain Marvel is not only going down as one of the biggest films of the year, but of the decade.

Lashana Lynch just had a significant role in it. Yet, her tag here stay dead. She has 39k followers on Instagram. 13k followers on Twitter. And where is her press? Only a few articles about her have come out in all this time leading up to the movie and after its release.

I only hope the industry is paying attention and this role does something to propel her career. But since Hollywood is a popularity contest and she’s still being paid dust for recognition I’m gonna have to pray to somebody’s God on that one.

#GiveLashanaherthings
